nt|^b@2^z@3
We have spent a lot of time considering the types of hands that are appropriate for a Michaels cuebid or an Unusual notrump overcall, but the advantages and disadvantages of using these conventions have not really been mentioned yet. 

It has been noted that there are alternative ways of bidding hands that contain at least 5-5 in 2 suits and enough strength to enter the bidding after an opponent opens at the 1-level. Since that is the case, why do we need these conventions at all? There are 2 reasons:

