Notice that the main disadvantage that most conventions suffer from does not really apply in the case of the Michaels cuebid or the Unusual 2NT overcall. Most conventions have the disadvantage of replacing a useful natural bid. As we saw when we first started studying these conventions, the natural bids that they replace are not very useful. Furthermore, we saw that there are other ways of bidding the types of hands that would have overcalled 2NT or cuebid the opener's suit.

So the question is: do the advantages of using Michaels cuebids and the Unusual notrump outweigh the disadvantages that these conventions have?

