at|Fortunately, it is not just the designers of SAYC who like these conventions. The majority of the world's serious bridge players (especially in North America) use both the Unusual notrump and Michaels cuebid conventions. 

Also, in the judgment of your author (for whatever that's worth), both of these conventions gain much more than they lose, especially if you use them with care. Do not use a Michaels cuebid or an Unusual 2NT overcall with a given hand just because you can. Wait until you have a hand with which the deck seems to be stacked in your favor (no pun intended) and then pounce!

